productEmsList.title: Installation
productEmsList.tooltip:
Transom Mount: These are attached to the back (transom) of a boat hull. Alternatively, use the included equipment to install on a trolling motor.

In-hull: An in-hull transducer is installed inside a boat hull against the bottom

productEmsList.title: ClearVü
productEmsList.tooltip:
260/455 kHz ClearVü is ideal for deeper water,  1000' Max Depth scanning sonar

455/800 kHz is the most flexible scanning sonar up to 500' max depth

Ultra-High Definition 800 kHz ClearVü is ideal for 200' Max depth Scanning sonar

productEmsList.title: SideVü
productEmsList.tooltip:
260/455 kHz SideVü is ideal for deeper water, up to 750' max depth

455/800 kHz is the most flexible scanning sonar up to 500' max depth

Ultra-High Deffinition 1200 kHz SideVü is ideal for 30' max depth

seo.ogDescription: The Garmin GT30-TM is a transom mount transducer that is ideal for a shallow water fisherman who wants CHIRP traditional and ClearVü scanning sonar.
seo.title: Garmin GT30-TM | Transducer for Shallow Water

specs.Transducer beamwidth:

SideVü: 1.1°x53° @ 455 kHZ and 0.7°x30° @ 800 kHz
specs.Transducer frequency: ClearVü/SideVü CHIRP 455 kHz (425-485 kHz) & 800 kHz (790-850 kHz)

overviewTab.content:
Perfect for the shallow water fisherman who want CHIRP ClearVü and CHIRP SideVü scanning sonar, this transom mount transducer consistently displays clear definition of objects, structure and fish below and to each side of the boat.

The 20 ft transducer cable with built-in fast response temperature sensor has a power rating of 500 W per element (1,500 W total); a depth of 750 ft (ClearVü) and 500 ft left and right (SideVü); an operating frequency of 455/800 kHz; and a 0 to 70 transom angle. Pair it with your GCV™ 10 black box sonar.

Transducer comes with installation instructions. Follow the instructions carefully to avoid damaging your boat.

overviewTab.content:
Perfect for the shallow water fisherman who want CHIRP ClearVü and CHIRP SideVü scanning sonar with a stainless steel stem, this 12-pin thru-hull transducer consistently displays clear definition of objects, structure and fish below and to each side of the boat.

The transducer with built-in fast response temperature sensor has a power rating of 500 W per element (1,500 W total); a depth of 750 ft (ClearVü) and 500 ft left and right (SideVü); an operating frequency of CHIRP 455/800 kHz¹; for hull deadrises less than 5 degrees. Pair it with your GCV™ 10 scanning sonar module.

Includes transducer with stainless steel stem, fairing block, isolation plate and bushings, extension cable, mounting hardware and installation instructions. Follow the instructions carefully to avoid damaging your boat.

¹CHIRP frequency bandwidth is 445 to 475 kHz and 805 to 840 kHz.

overviewTab.content:
Ultra High-Definition Sonar System Transom Mount Transducer

Add stunningly clear Ultra High-Definition ClearVü and Ultra High-Definition SideVü scanning sonar images to your compatible chartplotter. Plug directly into your 8600xsv or ECHOMAP Ultra series chartplotter or use the GCV 20 sonar module to display on other compatible chartplotters. It includes 3 arrays, including a downward-facing element, with frequencies ranging from 0.8 MHz (800 kHz) to 1.2 MHz (1,200 kHz).

Ultra High-Definition ClearVü Scanning

This mode provides brilliant image clarity of structure and fish below your boat at greater depths than other high-frequency scanning sonars by putting more power on targets via a downward-facing element.

Ultra High-Definition SideVü Scanning

This mode delivers stunningly clear images of structure and fish off to the sides of your boat. This makes it easy to scout a fishing area quickly, because you can see everything the first time with such amazing clarity.
